The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | The City Diary
                                                                                                               The City Diary
                Relatives, friends and neighbours of a patient ransacked parts of CMRI hospital on Sunday afternoon, hours after his death. Alipore resident Jiten Kumar Barelli, 34, was admitted to the hospital on July 28 after he suffered injuries in a road mishap. The doctor treating him had been saying since then that his condition was stable but he died on Sunday, claimed Barellis relatives. They gheraoed the doctor. A police contingent controlled the situation.    Three Sri Lankan nationals in their 20s, who arrived at Calcutta airport from Bangkok early on Sunday, were sent back on the charge of using forged Indian passports. Sivaraja Kajen, Sathaiya Seelan Sudhan, and T. Kalainesan took a Thai Airways flight to the city.    Nearly 150 residents of Birati and adjoining areas, under ward 4 of North Dum Dum Municipality, were admitted to BN Bose Hospital and Bhatpara State General Hospital with gastro-enteritis since Saturday evening. Most of the patients were discharged after treatment but at least 20 are critical. Sachindramohan Sarkar, the chairman of the municipality, said the water might have been contaminated because of leaks in the supply line. A round-the-clock medical camp was set up in the area.    Dipak Kumar Chatterjee, a 34-year-old pedestrian was knocked down by a private bus at the MG Road-CR Avenue crossing on Sunday evening. Police said Dipak, a resident of Seoraphuli, was rushed to Medical College and Hospital, where his condition was stated to be critical. He had suffered severe head injuries, said an officer. The driver fled leaving behind the vehicle.    Two groups of residents clashed on Rafi Ahmed Kidwai Road on Sunday morning over the parking of a motorcycle beside a shop. The men exchanged blows and threw stones at one another. A large contingent of police controlled the situation. No one was arrested.                                                                                                                                                                   
